<n-docbody><doc bill="Y"><content.metadata.block><cmd.identifiers><cmd.cites><cmd.second.line.cite><bop/><bos/>Multidistrict Lit Man § 3:10<eos/><eop/></cmd.second.line.cite></cmd.cites></cmd.identifiers></content.metadata.block><prop.block><prop.head toc-guid=""><bop/><bos/><headtext>Multidistrict Litigation Manual</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head><content.metadata.block><cmd.dates><cmd.currency.default iso.d="20190501"><bop/><bos/>May 2019 Update<eos/><eop/></cmd.currency.default></cmd.dates></content.metadata.block><author.line><bop/><bos/><author>David F. Herr[<footnote.reference refid="If200bdb16b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">a0</footnote.reference>]</author><eos/><eop/></author.line><prop.head toc-guid="I97b7f560933b11da99e2b07024dacc26"><bop/><bos/><label.name>Part</label.name><label.designator>I.</label.designator><headtext>Handling Cases Before the Judicial Panel on Multidistrict Litigation</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head><prop.head toc-guid="I9f85f1c0933b11da99e2b07024dacc26"><bop/><bos/><label.name>Chapter</label.name><label.designator>3.</label.designator><headtext>Powers of the Panel</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head></prop.block><message.block><include.copyright n-include_collection="w_wlnv_msg" n-include_guid="I1DA35ED81DD211B281BAD200220BDFCA">Copyright (c) 2017 Thomson/RIA All rights reserved.</include.copyright></message.block><section><section.front><doc.title toc-guid="I94ed81f9e1e311da9c26e67ca3b71335"><head parent="doc.title"><bop/><bos/><label.name>§ </label.name><label.designator>3:10.</label.designator><headtext>Limitations on Panel&apos;s power—No review function</headtext><eos/><eop/></head></doc.title></section.front><section.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>The Panel does not review the decisions of either the transferee court or the transferor court.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If200e4c06b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">1</footnote.reference>] Review of decisions of these courts is governed by the normal appeal procedures for decisions of those courts.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If200e4c16b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">2</footnote.reference>] The Panel has viewed this restriction literally and has consistently deferred to the decisions and discretion of these courts in deciding matters relating to the handling of the litigation.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></section.body></section><author.footnotes><footnote ID="If200bdb16b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>a0</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>Maslon Edelman Borman &amp; Brand, LLP, Minneapolis, Minnesota.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote></author.footnotes><footnote.block><footnote ID="If200e4c06b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>1</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext><cite.query w-src-number="0304913958" w-serial-number="1981114874" w-seq-number="00001" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000345" ID="I514bd7616b3e11e9bfe8894985907fa8">In re Data General Corp. Antitrust Litigation, 510 F. Supp. 1220 (J.P.M.L. 1979)</cite.query>.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote><footnote ID="If200e4c16b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>2</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>Appeal of decisions of the Panel is discussed in detail in Chapter 11. <eos/><bos/>That discussion includes a review of procedures for obtaining appellate review of decisions of the transferee and transferor courts.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote></footnote.block><content.metadata.block><cmd.royalty><cmd.copyright><bop/><bos/>Westlaw. © 2019 Thomson Reuters.  <eos/><bos/>No Claim to Orig. U.S. Govt. <eos/><bos/>Works.<eos/><eop/></cmd.copyright></cmd.royalty><cmd.identifiers><cmd.cites><cmd.first.line.cite><bop/><bos/>MDLITMAN § 3:10<eos/><eop/></cmd.first.line.cite></cmd.cites></cmd.identifiers></content.metadata.block></doc></n-docbody>
